You are a senior frontend developer. Implement `BatchFilterDropdown.tsx` (default export `BatchFilterDropdown`) as a React + TypeScript functional component.

Imports:
- `useState` from React
- `Batch` from `../lib/batchUtils`

Props:
- `batches: Batch[]`
- `selectedBatch: Batch | null`
- `onSelectBatch: (batch: Batch | null) => void`
- `onSyncBatch?: (batch: Batch) => void`
- `remainingCountByBatch?: Map<number, number>` (default `new Map()`)
- `disabled?: boolean` (default `false`)
- `showModuleList?: boolean` (default `false`)

Core behavior:
- Keep `expandedBatchId: number | null` state.
- If `batches.length <= 1`, return `null`.
- `selectedRemaining = selectedBatch ? (remainingCountByBatch.get(selectedBatch.id) ?? selectedBatch.modules.length) : 0`.
- `getDisplayName(filename)` must strip a trailing `_[A-Za-z]+.prompt`, then strip `.prompt`.

Compact mode (`showModuleList === false`):
- Render a horizontal row with:
  - `<select>` value `selectedBatch?.id ?? 'all'`, disabled by `disabled`
  - options: `All Batches ({batches.length})` and each `{batch.name} ({batch.modules.length} modules)`
- Select change:
  - `'all'` -> `onSelectBatch(null)`
  - else parse selected id, find batch, call `onSelectBatch(foundBatch || null)`
- If `selectedBatch`, show a color dot with inline `backgroundColor: selectedBatch.color` and title `{name}: {modules.length} modules`.
- If `selectedBatch && onSyncBatch`, show button `Sync Batch ({selectedRemaining})`; on click call `onSyncBatch(selectedBatch)`; disable when `disabled || selectedRemaining === 0`.

Expanded mode (`showModuleList === true`):
- Render each batch as a card.
- Per batch:
  - `isExpanded = expandedBatchId === batch.id`
  - `isSelected = selectedBatch?.id === batch.id`
  - `remaining = remainingCountByBatch.get(batch.id) ?? batch.modules.length`
- Header click toggles both selection and expansion:
  - `onSelectBatch(isSelected ? null : batch)`
  - `setExpandedBatchId(isExpanded ? null : batch.id)`
- Header contains color dot, batch name/count, chevron icon rotated when expanded.
- Expanded area:
  - scrollable module rows showing: index (`idx + 1`), truncated display name from `getDisplayName(module.filename)` (full filename in `title`), and `P{module.priority}`
  - if `onSyncBatch`, full-width button `Sync {batch.name} ({remaining} remaining)`; on click `stopPropagation()` then `onSyncBatch(batch)`; disabled when `disabled || remaining === 0`

Styling:
- Use Tailwind dark-theme classes.
- Sync buttons use active gradient `#FDCE49 -> #DFA84A`, hover `#FFD966 -> #FDCE49`, and muted disabled state.
- Include inline SVG refresh icons in both sync buttons.
